The cathedral for the diocese of Ossory. Well worth a visit for anybody interested in religious architecture, it was built in 1847, a recent edition was the installation of a gold ceiling above the altar. Otherwise it's a fully functioning Cathedral hosting masses, weddings, funerals, confirmations and confessions etc.

Do not miss the Museum of Contemporary Art in Bangkok! Not only is it a wonderful museum it is also a stunning piece of modern architecture. You'll need all day and then some more, a dream for any art buff there's five floors of spectacular exhibits. On the ground floor there's a restaurant, garden and an interactive experience. Take the family.  I loved it and next time I'm in Bangkok I'll be heading back for another look.👍🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟

The Museum of Contemporary Art is from 2012. It is a private museum housed in a large building. 

There is no double pricing. Same price for a Thai and a foreigner. If you  are more than 60, you can enter for free. Not only Thais, but also foreigners. The price for a regular ticket is TB 250.

Obviously, most of the items on display in this museum are from Thailand, but on the fifth floor there is an interesting collection of foreign items.

Next to all items on display is a label with information in Thai and in English. 

You are allowed to use a camera inside the museum, but you cannot use a flash. There is one exception: you are not allowed to take pictures inside the special Robert Green collection on the fifth floor.

There is a coffee shop on the ground floor. There is a car park in the basement. 

The staff are friendly and helpful.

If you are interested in contemporary art, this place is definitely worth a visit.

Oh....
This is an ....hard to say.
They declare that this is a contemporary museum but this museum does not explore the comprehensive contemporary art all over the world because it’s simply this is a private museum owned by one business man.the collection is rely on his taste.of course this museum is playing a key role for collecting national artists of Thailand but mainly the collection is reflected on his preference.
I really love this spot because I can enjoy the most sophisticated art works in Bangkok.
I’ll come back here again.

Great museum. 
Beautiful building. Lots of great surrealism and some traditional Thai art. 
Definitely worth going although it's hard to get to, since the nearby train is not operational yet. Try to make sure your cab driver knows the place. Took us some time to get there but was worth it 👍👍

Surprisingly beautiful (and modern) structure that houses mostly modern and some traditional art. Peacefully quiet—not many locals seem aware it exists. The art is fascinating—a modern reinterpreting traditional Thai aesthetic forms. Lovely reprieve from the hot chaos of the city.
When were there in 2016 when we took the freedom Cruise you are not able to go in but enjoy the breeze in the back. We also did a true of the orphanage which part of proceeds went to it.
It was lit! We enjoyed it!
Great locality for an outdoor wedding.
Under renovation but should become one of downtown's best place to visit starting in 2018.
Good

My 1st visit beautiful auditorium saw
EQUUS brilliant play, my friends said I wouldn't enjoy it but I loved it excellent acting.
One down point when actors were at back of stage it was a job to here what  they were saying and I was only in j5.
Went to The Greatest Shwoman Sing a long. It was lovely being able to go to something there at a reasonable price. Hope they do more of these. Ice creams are pricey though.
Lovely theatre. Seats better than most. Handy restaurants nearby

A great place to experience theatre, good acoustics, friendly staff and a really nice ambiance. 
The seating can be a bit cramped and access along the rows not easy, but the plus side is you can be really close to the stage and even at the rear of the stalls you are closer than in many west end top price seats. 
There is a restaurant and bars for pre-theatre food and drinks in subterranean surroundings (the old vaults), while these places have a great atmosphere they are totally impractical for disabled guests as all involve steps with no lifts  - yes I know the age and style of the building is a limitation but I would think at least one of the areas would be accessible?
Lovely theatre. Disabled access via a lift however the door sticks. Limited female loos so queues during the interval. Drinks and ice creams on the expensive side.
Friendly staff, nice food. We had a banquet for 7 people with a pile of beers. Loads of well prepared, tasty food and reasonably priced as well.
Really nice surroundings lovely friendly staff and great food.  Brilliant value for money.  Well worth a visit.
Fantastic food and friendly service. Only place that has good aromatic crispy duck. They make some great food.
Would give zero stars if possible. Food was terrible, and the service was even worse! Avoid like the plague.
Remember that You have to pay extra money for rice. Beef was... lets say "good" and the service really nice.

Don't order from here as if you fall asleep you don't get your order or your money back so please don't order from little Italy pizza really bad review go to pizza hut as its a lot better than this place

I moved out of Aberdeen a year ago and what a loss it is not to have Little Italy around.. I simply cannot find a pizza restaurant with the same quality pizzas as this.

Expand! And for every newcomers, I highly recommend the Little Italy Calzone 12" if you like a bit spicy food!
Their sizes are a bit on the small side but otherwise great value for your money.

I went and ordered food throigh their website. The order was rejected due to them being too busy which I totally understand. However they proceeded to charge me twice and took the money out of my account. I emailed them and have not received any response. I am really not happy with this and this is slmesomet that people need to be avare off

The pizza is very good. I would say 7/10. I have tried the piri piri one and calzone. The number of ingredients in calzone is perfect. No option to order garlic sauce. Only garlic mayo available which taste very average. It is so easy to make garlic sauce, it should be a problem for the pizza place. The delivery time was shocking, 1:35, during the week. I cannot imagine waiting time during the peak times. Furthermore, the place is quite dear. It is not real Italian pizza therefore price should be lower. Why do I need to pay extra fee while ordering online through your website. I see the potential but some changes must be done.
This was a very fun experience. It was really big and lots of superstars were there. I would  highly recommend taking a camera with you because you can take beautiful photos. 🤳

Madame Tussauds Amsterdam is the cool place to visit. It's very well organized. They also have captain marvel theme for kids and for the Marvel fans. They have nice art work and statue of lot of famous celebrity from film industry, music industry , sports industry. It was nice visit.
Great place. Worth a visit. Expensive but I guess it is not cheap to make and perhaps even royalties paid for the characters and figures. Children loved it too.

Had a lot of fun in this place. We went in January and it was mostly empty which was nice. Lots of interactive displays and cool things to look at. It was better than I expected. Go during off hours; I could see this place not being nearly as good if it were crowded.

Fun! Most of the wax figures look quite young so might need to be updated at some point. First Madame Tussauds I've been to. Sent a photo of me with Ryan Gosling to a friend and found out by chance she was in Amsterdam too so that was a wonderful surprise 😂

Great tasting dim-sum at bargain prices. Good selection of about 20 dishes, including all the favourites! This branch only has the Michelin Bib Gourmand so if you're looking for the starred branch you'll need to queue elsewhere. Very typical service for a dim-sum place so don't expect much! Cash only for paying the bill!
Great food, excellent service. Price... Very cheap. The baked pork buns are exceptional. So light and sweet. The fresh steamed shrimp dumplings were lovely. Whole shrimp. Yum
Pretty standard - I ended up preferring Dim Dim Sums dimsum offerings. Not really sure what the hype is around,  but it isn't bad food at all. Fairly good and at a low price point too.

the food is above average but not mind blowingly good. Their roast pork bun is definitely excellent and this is a must try but the other dishes were not very impressive. However, it is very cheap to eat here! So all things considered it’s got a very good value proposition. However, the service is absolutely abysmal.
No, don’t go there. I thought it was the same everyone was talking about, but we were slightly disappointed. There are places I  tried better dumplings.

One of the best Italian restaurants in Dublin,  in my opinion, for many years. Recently, the restaurant has been refurbished and is now even cosier and more comfortable than it used to be. Also, the menu is very keenly priced and the early-bird menu is especially good value with the Bellini thrown in at no extra charge. The Italian staff are all totally professional, efficient, friendly and welcoming.

The staff was nice and friendly but the dish I had wasn't that great. The presentation was very good but taste and texture could have been better.

Looking at the other reviews, everyone seems to like so maybe it was just me. I will try something different next time.

For everyone else, go there and make up you own mind.

Visited this restaurant by chance on a quiet weeknight. Service was superb as was the food. Mushroom ravioli was the best we’ve ever had compared to many other similar restaurants (our favourite dish). Reasonable prices for the area with many specials. We will definitely be back!

Excellent food and excellent service, went here for a family get together and went for the set menu. Everyone raved about the starters and main courses. Excellent wine too. Slightly disappointed I didn't get the pizza as it looked amazing going to other tables. I'll definitely be back for the pizza, I might be changing my review to five stars. Keep up the excellent work folks! Viva Italia!

Best Italian restaurant in Dublin. 
Definitely our favourite place to have meals whether it's just a quick lunch or romantic dinner!!!
Highly recommended! 10/10

Visited this place during a school field trip to my then elementary school child. Beautiful place. With lots of history. It was during the springtime and their were so many beautiful places to take pictures. All I can remember
My cousin got married here. It's a very traditional building. Nice for a small wedding or gathering.  My cousin loved it, and we had the time of our lives.
Very nice venue we visited for a friend's wedding, it was decorated for the holidays. A great historic venue
Love visiting Santa here!

A bar that offers happy hour in Fes, Morocco?  We had to check it out.

Great views of the garden on the terrace.  The cushions are a bit dirty and torn up but eh.  The service was slow but once it started to fill up, our server was around more.

The happy hour is kind of a joke.  Order 2 beers, get the 3rd free but only per person and they give you all 3 at the same time.

We enjoyed our evening of drinks and the best Hookah we’ve had so far in Morocco. This is the only ‘bar’ we found in the area.  Staff were really friendly and the wine was nice and cold. Shame we ran out of time and couldn’t make it back another night.
Nice location, more potential, alcohol available ;)

seems to be one of the few places to have a drink in Fes !  the prices are a little high but considering the alcohol shortage,  you cant complain.  They also have local Moroccan beer which is pretty good.
One of very little places you get an actual alcoholic drink and mine long island for 80dh was pretty juicy - read strong. Nice terrace on top, really cozy place.

Had a romantic dinner with my husband here for my birthday. Beautiful restaurant, wonderful staff, delicious food and drinks. Waitress (can’t recall her name, I think it was Jeannine) was knowledgeable, funny, and personal. My husband had the special, it was halibut, which was tasty but very small portioning. My plate had large portions so I guess it depends on what you order. Overall the experience was great!

My friend and I love discovering new places especially when we travel. I found this online before we went to Rome and booked for dinner. We ended up having breakfast twice and lunch twice.. If you love your açai bowls or your smoothies in the morning, this is perfect, if you love pancakes, then this is for you too, of course the menu has more to offer. Here’s just a selection of what we tried. Everyone needs to try this place. Delicious
One of my favorite small downtown restaurants.  Great lunch and dinner.  Unique and flavorful dishes.  Great service and atmosphere.  Parking can be tricky during busy times.

The bartenders here make some rad drinks for sure! I’m not a mixed drink kind of person but that’s all I order at this restaurant. They put on a show and give you some attitude....in a good way! The beef curry is the best I’ve ever had.....Great restaurant!
the service and drinks were exceptional.  but I didnt really like what I ordered. next time I'll get something else. but the dragon drink is amazing!!!
